The variable speed command, vs, will change the speed, and therefore
the duration, of an audio passage by a factor of 0.8 to 2.0.  Type vs,
a space, and the factor by which the speed should change.  The effect
will not change the pitch of the audio, but only its speed, or duration.
Instead of a speed factor, you may type the desired duration as a time
value.  a time value must have an M separating minutes and seconds,
and may have an H separating hours from minutes.

